<subSubSection id="EC6EACC8ABD70CBC9E94784399E982BA" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="067022D2D73C1814C7BF9C0E10433D8B" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="97B2F9E59772FA9CAD37D07AD2615D1B" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">
On the base of molecular results, 
<bibRefCitation id="F0DD27EA076F7F546E620442D09EAD95" author="Haase, M" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Molluscan studies" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="101 - 105" publicationUrl="10.1093/mollus/eyp051" refId="B29" refString="Haase, M, Naser, MD, Wilke, T, 2010. Ecrobia grimmi in brackish Lake Sawa, Iraq: indirect evidence for long-distance dispersal of hydrobiid gastropods (Caenogastropoda: Rissooidea) by birds. Journal of Molluscan studies 76: 101 - 105, 10.1093/mollus/eyp051" title="Ecrobia grimmi in brackish Lake Sawa, Iraq: indirect evidence for long-distance dispersal of hydrobiid gastropods (Caenogastropoda: Rissooidea) by birds." url="10.1093/mollus/eyp051" volume="76" year="2010">Haase et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="C83C811799A0914959DFE6ABEB3CD998" baseAuthorityName="Clessin &amp; Dybowski" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Ecrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="grimmi">
<emphasis id="7120A34D03F907357A491957D99A2DE7" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Ecrobia grimmi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the mixomesohaline Lake Sawa (Iraq) was possibly transported by migrating birds from the Caspian Sea. The identification of our material of 
<taxonomicName id="5EC98174A31259E607806B14F5C5128B" baseAuthorityName="Clessin &amp; Dybowski" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Ecrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="grimmi">
<emphasis id="6375C90D9F922CAABCD40C79523320A4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Ecrobia grimmi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well of 
<taxonomicName id="86B3F6AD6DFAB00787056E7075EDE45C" baseAuthorityName="Radoman" baseAuthorityYear="1974" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochliopidae" genus="Heleobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dalmatica">
<emphasis id="502B5B413DA03AB320C927CA4833EF0F" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Heleobia dalmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was confirmed by using molecular techniques (Martin Haase pers. communication). An analysis of the specimens from NHMW published by 
<bibRefCitation id="E3ECEF8D9299AFF5C3368980984F3F98" author="Starmuehlner, F" journalOrPublisher="Sitzungsberichte der oesterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, mathematisch-naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, Abteilung I," pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B57" refString="Starmuehlner, F, Edlauer, A, 1957. Ergebnisse der Oesterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949/50 (Mit Beruecksichtigung der Ausbeute der Oesterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1956): Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Molluskenfauna des Iran. Sitzungsberichte der oesterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, mathematisch-naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, Abteilung I, 166 (9/10): 435-494." title="Ergebnisse der Oesterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949 / 50 (Mit Beruecksichtigung der Ausbeute der Oesterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1956): Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Molluskenfauna des Iran. Sitzungsberichte der oesterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, mathematisch-naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, Abteilung I, 166 (9 / 10): 435 - 494." year="1957">
<normalizedToken id="8648522559178102C8E49FC650A90CD4" originalValue="Starmühlner">Starmuehlner</normalizedToken>
and Edlauer (1957)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="B38D0EB6D605E8BC7B521391FB95DA74" baseAuthorityName="Draparnaud" baseAuthorityYear="1805" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Hydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis id="49BABFED324B2DD82A2A7E00E2CD3A0F" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Hydrobia acuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows that these specimens probably belong to 
<taxonomicName id="CA8F6F7B1B999FFCA93B9BA59880823E" baseAuthorityName="Clessin &amp; Dybowski" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Ecrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="grimmi">
<emphasis id="75C62F75D522550F556A145AF32A16FC" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Ecrobia grimmi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation id="C78A4BF29FDD7C024B087D77398E521C" captionStart="" captionStartId="F8" captionText=". Figure 8. The molluscs of brackish waters. a Ecrobia grimmi b Heleobia dalmatica c Ecrobia grimmi from Edlauer's collection (NHMW, &quot; Hydrobia acuta &quot; 75000 / E / 60453) d Cerithidea cingulata." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/20810" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Fig. 8c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
